ingredients.Name: stew meat, cut into 1 inch cubes
large carrots, cut diagonally into 1/2 inch thick slices
beef broth (or sub 2 tsp Knorr Beef Bouillon + 3 cups of water)
all purpose flour (can sub a 1:1 gluten free flour)

directions.Direction: Heat olive oil in a large cast iron skillet over medium heat.

Season beef with salt and pepper, to taste. Add beef to the skillet and cook until evenly browned, about 2-3 minutes. Alternatively, if you have a slow cooker that you can sauté in, you can sauté the beef directly in the slow cooker.

Place beef, potatoes, carrots, onion and garlic into a 6-qt slow cooker. Stir in beef broth, tomato paste, coconut aminos, thyme, rosemary, paprika, and bay leaves until well combined; season with salt and pepper, to taste.
Cover and cook on low heat for 7-8 hours or high heat for 3-4 hours.
In a small bowl, whisk together flour and 1/2 cup stew broth.
Stir the flour mixture into the slow cooker. Cover and cook on high heat for an additional 30 minutes, or until broth has thickened.
Serve with crusty bread and garnish with fresh parsley, if desired.
Enjoy!

Push chicken to the side of the pan and add in beaten eggs. Scramble them and incorporate them with chicken.
Add shredded carrots, peanuts, noodles and sauce to the pan and mix well.
Mix in lime juice.

Add beef back to the pan.
Pour in sauce mixture and bring to a boil for 1-2 minutes until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice/ cauliflower rice.
Top with green onions and sesame seeds.

Add coleslaw mixture, coconut aminos and sauté for a few minutes. Add little more aminos if mixture isn't well coated.
Make a well in the center and add in egg/s and scramble
Mix in Sriracha.

Top with sauce, green onions & sesame seeds.
Enjoy!

Grill corn on high heat for about 5 minutes, rotating frequently until corn begins to char.

Meanwhile prepare dressing by whisking together ingredients in a bowl, adding 1 tbs of water at a time until a dressing consistency is achieved.
In a large bowl toss together baby kale, corn, queso fresco, shredded chicken (optional) cilantro and dressing.
Serve and top with red onions, pumpkin seeds, and avocado slices. Enjoy!

Cut charred pineapple squares into small chunks, mix together with other salsa ingredients, and set aside.

Top steaks with pineapple salsa and serve with coconut rice. Enjoy!

Toss spinach, cucumber, avocado, basil, dill and walnuts together in a bowl and toss to combine.
Serve and top with filet, dressing, cheese, and fresh herbs (optional) in that order.
Enjoy!

coconut cream (or heavy whipping cream for dairy version)

Add back chicken thighs to the pan with the crispy side up. Baste chicken thighs in sauce and remove from heat.
Scatter parsley and tarragon over chicken and sauce.

12oz cooked fettuccine noodles of choice (I used gluten  free)

Add the cauliflower and chicken stock and bring the pot to a boil. Cover the pot, reduce the heat, and simmer for 5 minutes, until the cauliflower is soft.

Cook chicken breasts in large saucepan with olive oil over medium-high heat for 5-7 minutes on each side, or until internal temp of 165 F is reached.
Remove from pan and let cool.
In the same pan add spinach with a little olive oil and sauté until cooked.
Add cooked noodles and sauce and heat over medium heat.
Once warm, remove from stove, and top with sliced chicken breast, grated parmesan and fresh parsley.
Enjoy!

Add pasta to the pan and mix well.
Top with Parmesan and sage leaves.

directions.Direction: Drain the excess water from the tofu by wrapping it in paper towels, placing on a plate, covering with another plate, and placing a heavy object on top. Let drain for 20-30 minutes. Alternatively, you could also use a tofu press if you have one.

Prep the seasoning mix in a small mixing bowl and set aside.
Prep your peppers, onions and scallions.

In batches, toss the tofu cubes into the coating and mix until well coated. I did this in 3 separate batches.
Heat 2 tbs neutral oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat and add tofu cubes in batches, insuring not to overcrowd the pan.
Pan fry tofu for about 3 minutes on each side, or until crispy. Remove from pan and set aside on a plate.
Once you have pan fried all of the tofu, wipe the pan clean and add 2 tbs of fresh oil.

Let everything cook down for 3-4 minutes, or until garlic becomes brown and crispy.
Then add in the sliced scallions and cook for an additional minute.
Next add in the crispy tofu cubes and seasoning mix. Mix well until everything is coated.
Serve over rice with steamed (or sautéd) green beans and top with additional scallions.
Enjoy!

Transfer to a plate and set aside.

Let cook for about 5 more minutes, or until chicken has cooked all the way through and sauce has thickened up a bit.
Taste and season with salt and pepper as needed.
Serve over mashed potatoes (or rice), top with fresh parsley and enjoy!

ingredients.Name: Sriracha (or any hot sauce you like)
cauliflower rice (or sub cooked white rice)
fresh parsley, chopped (plus more for garnish)

Add the riced cauliflower (or cooked white rice) to the skillet and stir to mix everything together well and coat in melted butter. Cook, stirring regularly for 1 minute.

Serve over cauliflower rice (or white rice) and garnish with more salt +pepper (if needed) and fresh parsley. Enjoy!

tamari (or soy sauce for non gf)

Transfer cooked rice to pan with garlicky kale and stir to combine. Season with additional salt + pepper if needed.

gluten free breadcrumbs (I used cauli crunch)
dry white wine or chicken broth
mashed potatoes or cauliflower mash (they have them both in the frozen section at TJ's)

Lower the heat and add the meatballs back to the pan. Toss meatballs in sauce to coat.
Cover and simmer until the meatballs are cooked through and are no longer pink in the center, about 5 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes or cauliflower mash with a side of green beans (or veggies of choice).
Spoon additional sauce over meatballs and top with reserved chopped parsley.
Enjoy!

red bell pepper, cut into 1 inch cubes
green bell pepper, cut into 1 inch cubes
white onion, cut into 1 inch cubes
sugar (can use coconut or brown sugar too)

Simmer for 1-2 minutes until the sauce starts to thicken, then stir to coat meat and veggies in sauce.
Serve over rice and garnish with green onions and sesame seeds.

medium red onion, halved and thinly sliced

ingredients.Name: juice from  large oranges (or sub 1 cup of store bought OJ)
coconut aminos or gluten free soy sauce
arrowroot starch (or cornstarch), dissolved in 2 tbs water
scallions, whites thinly sliced, greens cut into 2 inch pieces

Add the orange-honey sauce mixture and the orange zest and cook, stirring, until thickened, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add the cooked shrimp back to the skillet, along with the scallion greens, and toss to coat the shrimp with the sauce.
Serve over rice, topping with additional scallions and/or red pepper flakes if desired.

Name: Creamy Lemon Pepper Chicken & Gnocchi
Description: Tender chicken breasts in a creamy, lemon sauce with gnocchi and spinach make for the perfect comforting one pot dinner! I used gluten-free gnocchi and a dairy-free heavy cream but the recipe can easily be modified depending on your dietary preferences :)

ingredients.Name: large shallot, thinly sliced into rings
red curry paste (I used a mild one)
boneless, skinless cod fillets, cut into 4 even pieces

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 300 F.
Heat large saucepan over medium heat, add avocado oil and shallot. Cook shallot for about 5 minutes or until browned, stirring occasionally insuring not to burn.
Remove shallots from skillet using a slotted spoon and season with salt. Set aside.
In the same pan over medium-high heat, add ginger and curry paste. Cook for about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and coconut cream and bring to a simmer. Cook for about 6-8 minutes, or until tomatoes begin to burst. Remove pan from heat.

Season cod generously with salt and pepper. Arrange cod fillets over tomato mixture. Transfer pan to the oven and bake for 20 minutes, or until fish is cooked all of the way through. It should be opaque and flakey.
Serve over rice or cauliflower rice and top with crispy shallots.
Garnish with lime juice and fresh basil. Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Coconut-Tomato Curry Cod
Description: I'm not a huge seafood person myself but this cod is something I dream about! It's rich and creamy with the perfect amount of sweetness from the cherry tomatoes. An easy and healthy one pot dinner the whole family will enjoy 😋

ingredients.Name: plain unsweetened yogurt (I used the TJ's cashew one)
tomato puree (or tomatoe sauce in a can)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400 F. Mix the marinade ingredients together in a large bowl. Add the chicken thighs, toss well to ensure they are coated evenly. Place in the refrigerator to marinate for 30 mins - 1 hour while you prepare the sauce. Or if you plan ahead, you can marinate the chicken overnight.
Mix sauce ingredients together in a large baking dish and bake for 15 minutes uncovered.
Remove from oven and add the marinated chicken thighs to the baking dish, coating them well in the sauce.
Return the baking dish bake to the oven and cook for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 5 minutes, then serve over rice and top with extra sauce and cilantro. Serve with naan or tortillas if desired.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: One Pan Butter Chicken (Easy)
Description: If you love butter chicken, you're going to love this easy, fool-proof butter chicken that comes together in just one pan! All of the classic butter chicken flavor you love with minimal effort and minimal cleanup... yes please!

ingredients.Name: grape tomatoes, sliced in half lengthwise
cream of choice (or sub milk of choice + arrowroot starch I used light coconut milk)

directions.Direction: Fillet the chicken breasts into two thinner pieces so you have 4 breasts in total.
Season the chicken with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning on both sides.

Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add 1 Tbsp avocado oil and swirl to coat the surface. Add the chicken to the skillet and cook on each side until golden brown and cooked through, about 4 minutes on each side. Remove the chicken from the pan and set aside.

Turn the heat down to medium-low and let the pan cool down a but before adding the remaining avocado oil. Then add the minced garlic and halved grape tomatoes. Sauté for a few minutes, then add the spinach and mix well until spinach wilts.
If using: Add the arrowroot starch to the milk and mix well.
Mix in the milk + arrowroot starch mixture or cream of choice and pesto.
Mix well and bring to a simmer.
Add back in the chicken and toss to coat well in the sauce.
Top with fresh grated parmesan and serve over rice or pasta.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Creamy Pesto Chicken
Description: Tender chicken breasts in a creamy pesto sauce with juicy tomatoes make for the perfect minimal-effort summer dinner! Serves perfectly over pasta or with some rice :)
Notes: The milk + arrowroot starch is a lighter option if you don't want all of the calories from a heavy cream or coconut cream and yields the same results :)

ingredients.Name: 14 oz can quartered artichoke hearts, drained
Freshly ground black pepper, to taste

directions.Direction: Preheat the oven to 400º F.
Add the chicken thighs and 1/4 cup pesto to a bowl. Toss to coat then let marinate for 15-20 minutes on the counter or up to overnight in the fridge.

Heat a large, oven-safe skillet over medium heat. When hot, add the 1 tbs oil and place the chicken thighs face down in the skillet. Cook for 4-5 minutes, until golden brown. Transfer the thighs to a plate and set aside.
Still over medium heat, add the remaining 1 tbs avocado oil to the skillet, then add the garlic, rice and oregano. Toast for 3-4 minutes, until fragrant.
Add the artichoke hearts, olives, stock, salt and a few grinds of freshly ground black pepper. Bring to a simmer then arrange the chicken thighs on top.
Transfer to the oven to bake, uncovered, for about 25 minutes or until the chicken has cooked through and the rice is tender.
To serve, toss the rice with the remaining pesto. Top with fresh basil sprigs and a more freshly ground black pepper if desired.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: One Pot Pesto Chicken and Rice
Description: This easy one skillet meal is made with tender chicken thighs, pesto, artichoke hearts, green olives and rice. An easy, flavorful dinner that’s ready in just about 30 minutes!

ingredients.Name: large yellow or white onion, chopped
green bell pepper halved, seeded and sliced
garlic cloves, finely grated or minced
lime wedges, sweet peppers, sour cream and sliced avocado, for serving

directions.Direction: Heat the oven to 375 F.
Season the chicken with salt and pepper on both sides. Heat the avocado oil in a 10-inch skillet (the pan size is very important) over medium-high.
Brown the chicken on both sides to give it good color, about 2 minutes per side. Transfer to a plate.
Add the onion and bell peppers to the pan and sauté until just starting to soften, about 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Add the green chiles, cinnamon, garlic and cumin to the skillet and cook for about 2 minutes, then add the black beans and cherry tomatoes. Season generously with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle the rice on top in an even layer. **It’s important that the black beans are beneath the rice and chicken. The rice will burn otherwise.
Add the stock and return the chicken thighs to the pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes, until the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked. Sprinkle with the cilantro.
Serve with lime wedges, sweet peppers, sour cream and avocado. Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Mexican Chicken & Rice Skillet
Description: An easy one pot dinner packed with protein, veggies and tons of flavor!

ingredients.Name: boneless skinless chicken breasts, diced into bite size pieces
Dano's Cheesoning Blend, divided (or sub a mixture of 1 tbs Italian seasoning, 1 tsp garlic powder,  1/2 tsp onion powder, 1 tsp salt, 1/2 tsp pepper)
small zucchini, sliced into half moons
small yellow squash, sliced into half moons
grated parmesan, plus more to taste

directions.Direction: In a mixing bowl, season chicken pieces with Dano's Cheesoning Blend (or half of your homemade seasoning blend).

Melt 1 tbs butter in pan with 1 tbs avocado oil over medium-high heat, then add the chicken and cook for about 3 minutes on each side, or until the chicken has cooked through. Transfer chicken to a plate or bowl and tent with foil to keep warm.

Heat remaining 1 Tbsp oil and 1 Tbsp butter in the same skillet over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and squash, then season with remaining 1 tbs of seasoning blend. Cook tossing occasionally until just tender, about 4 minutes.
Return chicken to pan with zucchini and squash. Squeeze in lemon juice, parmesan and parsley and toss to mix. Season with additional salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or cooked orzo and garnish with additional Parmesan + parsley if desired.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Lemon Parmesan Chicken & Squash Skillet
Description: A super easy, flavorful, one pan chicken and veggie recipe everyone will enjoy :) A cheesy, lemony and garlicky dinner that makes great leftovers too!

directions.Direction: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium- high heat.
Add onions and garlic, and sauté for 2-3 minutes or until fragrant.
Add ground turkey, and brown for 7-8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until meat is no longer pink and onions are translucent.

Add sweet potato, Italian seasoning, coriander, salt and black pepper. Stir to combine, then add the 2 tbs of water. Turn heat to low and COVER. Let simmer for 10 minutes, or just until potatoes are soft.
Add baby spinach and Parmesan cheese and stir.
Turn off the heat. Add shredded mozzarella, and cover for 3 more minutes to allow the cheese to melt and the spinach to wilt.
Garnish with fresh parsley, serve and enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Ground Turkey Sweet Potato Skillet
Description: Ground turkey seasoned with spices, steamed sweet potatoes, spinach and cheese come together in one pan to make an easy, protein-packed skillet the whole family will enjoy!

ingredients.Name: chopped fresh thyme, plus more for garnish

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400 F.

Season the chicken with salt and pepper, then rub the flat side with flour to coat. Heat a large oven-safe pan over high heat, add 1 tbs of avocado oil and sear the chicken thighs face down for about 5 minutes, or until golden brown. Remove the chicken to a plate.

Add the butter and onions and cook for about 5 minutes, or until softened. Add a 1/2 cup apple cider, season with salt and pepper, and continue cooking another 5-8 minutes, until the cider has evaporated and the onions are lightly golden.
Add the mushrooms, garlic, thyme, and sage, then add the chicken thighs back to the pan. Add the remaining 1 1/2 cups cider, and chicken broth.
Transfer the pan to the oven and roast for 30 minutes or until the chicken is fully cooked.
Serve the chicken thighs over a bed of mashed potatoes and drizzle with any remaining pan sauce and onion/mushroom mixture. Garnish with fresh thyme sprigs if desired.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Apple Cider Chicken Thighs
Description: Tender apple cider chicken thighs, caramelized onions, and mushrooms come together in just one pan for the perfect easy one pan fall dinner!

ingredients.Name: (17.3 ounce) package frozen puff pastry sheets, thawed and cut into 3" x 3" squares (can substitute gluten free puff pastry)
all purpose flour (can sub a 1:1 gluten free flour)
chicken bone broth (or sub regular chicken broth)
fresh thyme, chopped, plus more for garnish

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Melt butter in an ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Add leek and carrots, stirring often, until softened, about 6 minutes. Sprinkle with flour; cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Stir in broth and bring mixture to a simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in chicken, peas, cream, Dijon, parsley, thyme, salt, and pepper. Remove from heat.
Whisk together egg and 1 tablespoon water in a small bowl.
Brush pastry squares with egg wash.
Arrange squares on top of chicken mixture in the skillet, slightly overlapping so entire surface of chicken mixture is covered.
Place skillet on a rimmed baking sheet and bake for about 20 minutes, or until top is browned and filling is bubbly.
Remove from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with fresh thyme leaves and serve.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Skillet Chicken & Leek Pot Pie
Description: This easy one pan chicken pot pie is the ultimate comfort meal the whole family will enjoy! A few shortcuts including using rotisserie chicken and puff pastry make this an easy, no-fuss weeknight dinner that comes together in under an hour.

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400°F. Generously season chicken thighs with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Heat oil in a large, oven-proof skillet over medium-high heat. Sear chicken thighs for 3 minutes each side, until golden brown.
Add minced garlic to the same pan around the chicken and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.
Add the honey, both mustards, and water to the pan, mixing well, and combine all around the chicken.
Add in the potatoes and mix them through the sauce. Season with a bit more salt and pepper.
Allow the honey mustard sauce to simmer for two minutes, then transfer to the hot oven and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove the pan from the oven and add in the green beans (mixing them through the sauce). Return to the oven to bake for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until the potatoes are fork tender.
Garnish with fresh rosemary and serve.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Honey Mustard Chicken & Potatoes
Description: Juicy, chicken thighs are cooked in the best honey mustard sauce, surrounded by green beans and potatoes for a complete, hearty weeknight meal!

ingredients.Name: large boneless, skinless chicken breasts, butterflied in half to make 4 pieces
chicken broth (or sub bone broth for extra protein)
juice of  lemon, plus more to taste
mashed potatoes (I buy them premade for convenience), for serving

directions.Direction: Sprinkle both sides of each piece of chicken lightly with salt, pepper, and garlic powder.

Warm the olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Once the butter melts, add the chicken and cook for 3-4 minutes on each side, until it forms a nice golden crust and is cooked through.
Remove chicken to a plate and set aside.

Reduce heat to medium and add the remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Add the onion and cook for 2-3 minutes. Using the back of a knife, smash half of the garlic cloves, then add both the smashed and whole cloves to the pan with the onions.

Cook 2-3 minutes more, until the garlic is fragrant and lightly browned on the outside, then add chicken broth, lemon juice, and thyme. Scrape the bottom of the pan to deglaze any browned bits, and let the sauce simmer for about 4 minutes. It should be noticeably reduced.
Reduce heat again to medium-low, then stir in the cream. Return chicken to the skillet and let everything simmer gently for 2-3 minutes to blend the flavors.
Spoon the sauce over the chicken breasts and serve with mashed potatoes and green beans.
Garnish with fresh parsley and lemon wedges. Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Creamy Garlic Chicken Breasts
Description: Tender chicken breasts smothered in a garlic cream sauce comes together in one pan in just under 30 minutes!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425 F.
Toss halved baby potatoes in a bowl with 2 tbs olive oil, 2 tbs balsamic vinegar, 1/2 tbs minced garlic, 1/2 tbs italian seasoning, and 1/2 tbs salt.
Toss potatoes on parchment paper lined sheet pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile use the same bowl you tossed potatoes in and add green beans, tomatoes, and chicken strips.
Then add 3 tbs olive oil, 3 tbs balsamic vinegar, 1 tbs minced garlic, 1 tbs Italian seasoning and 1 tsp salt.
When potatoes come out, add remaining ingredients to the sheet pan and spread out in a single layer.
Top with Parmesan and bake for additional 20-25 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and potatoes are tender.
Top with fresh basil and enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Tuscan Chicken, Potatoes and Veggies
Description: This is probably one of the easier sheet pan meals I've made so far and it's relatively healthy too! You get the heartiness of meat and potatoes balanced by the fresh veggies and Italian flavors.

ingredients.Name: cheese of choice (mozzarella for classic... I used cheddar goat for dairy free)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400 F.
Chop baby potatoes in half, coat in olive oil, salt and place on sheet pan.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile chop asparagus, tomatoes and fresh basil and set aside.
Prepare chicken breasts in a bowl by seasoning with olive oil, salt, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Once potatoes are done, remove sheet pan from oven and add asparagus to sheet pan. Mix well and season with additional olive oil and salt.
Then push potatoes and asparagus to the sides making room in the center for the chicken breasts.
Place chicken breasts in the center of the sheet pan and top each breast with cheese, tomatoes sliced and fresh basil.
Bake sheet pan in oven for additional 25-30 minutes or until chicken breasts have reached internal temperature of 165 F.
Remove from oven and top chicken breasts with balsamic glaze.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Caprese Chicken and Veggies
Description: Is there anything better than Caprese in the summertime? Personally, I think not. Now add some chicken, potatoes and veggies and BAM you've got a delicious summertime sheet pan dinner.

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425 F.
Mix marinade ingredients together in a large bowl.
Reserving about 1/4 cup of the marinade in a separate bowl.
Toss chicken thighs in bowl with marinade and refrigerate while you prepare the potatoes and veggies.
Toss halved baby potatoes in bowl with 1/4 cup of marinade.
Spread potatoes on a sheet pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile prep your veggies and toss sliced onion, zucchini and baby tomatoes together in the same bowl the potatoes were in.
When potatoes are done, add veggies to the pan, incorporating well with the potatoes.
Then add marinated chicken thighs to the center of the pan.
*make sure chicken has marinated in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes, but closer to 1 hour is ideal*
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and add feta.
Bake for an additional 5 minutes.
Broil for 2-3 minutes at the end.
Top with fresh parsley and lemon.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Greek Chicken and Veggies
Description: All of the delicious greek flavors come together on one sheet pan for a flavor explosion in your mouth (yum). The key here is the marinade... it's so yummy and adds so much flavor!

ingredients.Name: beef hot dogs, cut into chunks
medium carrots, peeled and cut into coins
medium yellow onion, cut into chunks

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425 F. Line baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.
Toss potatoes, carrots and onions together in a bowl with 1-2 tbs olive oil, garlic powder, paprika, and salt.
Spread onto prepared sheet pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and add bell peppers and hot dog pieces. Mix well and return to oven.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes, or until hot dog pieces start to blister.
Serve and top with ketchup and green onions.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Hot Dog Hash
Description: This is basically an elevated way to eat a hot dog sans bun and it's absolutely delicious 😋 An easy weeknight dinner the whole family will enjoy! And hey, if you aren't a hot dog fan you can substitute chicken sausage or plant based sausage too.

ingredients.Name: almond milk ( or milk of choice)
cheese of choice (provolone is classic, but I subbed a dairy free one)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425 F.
In a large bowl, mix together marinade ingredients until well combined.
Add in steak, onions and bell peppers, and stir to coat.
Spread mixture on a sheet pan and cook for 15 minutes, or until steak is cooked through.
While sheet pan cooks, prepare the cheese sauce.

Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add flour and stir until a thick paste forms. Slowly pour in milk, while continuing to stir. Then add in cheese, mustard, coconut aminos, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt. Continue to stir until cheese has melted and sauce has thickened... about 3 minutes.
Serve meat and veggie mixture over toasted hoagie rolls and drizzle with cheese sauce.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Sheet Pan Philly Cheesesteak
Description: Juicy marinated meat, fresh peppers and onions all served over a toasty bun with some cheese sauce... comforting, easy and delicious! You're not going to want to skip this one... trust me :) It can also be made gluten and/or dairy free!

ingredients.Name: baby potatoes, cut into small pieces

directions.Direction: In a large bowl mix together apricot preserves, coconut aminos, balsamic vinegar, minced garlic, and ginger powder.
Reserve 1/4 cup of marinade and set aside.
To the large bowl add your chicken thighs and mix to coat well.
Let marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, but up to 24 hours (ideal for more flavor).
Preheat oven to 425 F.
Add diced baby potatoes to sheet pan and coat with olive oil and salt.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove sheet pan from oven and add cauliflower florets and onions. Toss with additional olive oil and salt.
Push veggies and potatoes to the side to make room for the chicken thighs in the center of the sheet pan.
Add marinated chicken thighs to the center of the sheet pan and bake for an additional 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top chicken breasts with additional marinade.
Turn oven on broil and return to oven for an additional 5 minutes to help crisp up the chicken (watching carefully to make sure it doesn't burn).
Top with cilantro and red pepper flakes.
Serve and enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Apricot Chicken & Veggies
Description: Are you sick of boring chicken and veggies? Step up your chicken sheet pan meal game with this easy, but delicious apricot chicken. The perfect combo of sweet and salty that is sure to satisfy all of your taste buds :)

ingredients.Name: chicken breast (about 4 large chicken breasts, halved)
gluten free flour (or flour of choice)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400 F.
Cut chicken breasts in half lengthwise to form chicken cutlets about 1/2" thick.
Salt chicken all over, then coat with flour, egg wash, followed by crushed corn flakes and place on a sheet pan.
Spray both sides of chicken with oil.
Then add asparagus and coat with oil and salt.
Bake sheet pan for 22-25 minutes, or until chicken is fully cooked and reaches an internal temperature of 165 F.
When sheet pan is about 5 mins out from being done, heat a saucepan over medium heat and mix together sauce ingredients. Bring to a simmer and let thicken. Remove from heat and set aside.
Once chicken is fully cooked and slightly cooled, add each chicken cutlet to the saucepan coating generously with sauce.
Serve chicken on a bed of rice with asparagus.
Top with sesame seeds, green onions, and sriracha mayo. Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Crispy Honey Garlic Chicken
Description: This is officially my new favorite way to eat chicken... it's crispy, garlicky, sweet and savory. Basically just one big flavor explosion in your mouth :) And minimal ingredients are required making it the perfect easy weeknight dinner!

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 475 F.
On a sheet pan, toss together the steak, shallots, flour, and salt + pepper. Add 1 tablespoon oil, tossing to coat.
Arrange the steak to one side of the baking sheet. Add the broccoli to the other side. Toss with oil, salt, and pepper. Bake for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, whisk together sauce ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour 2/3 of the sauce over the steak, toss it in the sauce to coat well. Switch the oven to broil. Broil for about 3 minutes, or until the meat is crisping. Watch closely.
In a bowl, toss together the cucumbers with the green onions, sesame oil, chili flakes, and salt.
Serve the beef and broccoli over rice and top with extra sauce, cucumber salad, spicy mayo, green onions, and sesame seeds.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Sheet Pan Beef and Broccoli
Description: This easy healthier baked beef and broccoli is full of flavor and comes together with minimal prep work (and dishes)... yay! It's gluten free too :) You're going to love it 😋

ingredients.Name: breadcrumbs of choice ( I used gluten free)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 450 F.
Mix breadcrumbs with 1 tsp salt.
Half chicken breasts lengthwise and dip in egg mixture, followed by breadcrumb mixture, then place on sheet pan.
Mix brussels with olive oil and 1 tsp salt and assemble on sheet pan next to the chicken. If there's not enough room on the pan, use two separate sheet pans.
***Spray chicken with oil (this is very important for crispy chicken).
Bake brussels and chicken in oven for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile prepare the sauce.
Once chicken and brussels sprouts are done remove from oven and reduce oven temperature to 400 F.
Top chicken breasts with sauce then return to oven and bake with brussels for an additional 5 minutes.
Top chicken with fresh thyme, and serve chicken with extra sauce, and brussels.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Hot Honey Mustard Chicken and Brussels
Description: Looking for a fun way to elevate some boring chicken? Think sweet and slightly spicy, crispy chicken with some roasted brussels... I mean yum! It only takes about 20 minutes too :)

ingredients.Name: medium butternut squash (peeled and cubed ~ 6 cups total)
14 ounce can full fat coconut milk
vegetable broth (or less for a thicker soup)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400 F.
Toss squash, onions, and garlic cloves on a sheet pan and drizzle with olive oil and a pinch of salt.
Drain and rinse chickpeas and toss on a separate sheet pan. Pat dry with paper towel and drizzle with olive oil and a pinch of salt.
Place both sheet pans in the oven and roast for about 30 minutes, or until squash and onions are tender and chickpeas are golden brown and crisp.
Remove both sheet pans from the oven and set chickpeas aside.
Transfer the squash, onions and garlic to a high speed blender along with the coconut milk, curry powder, maple syrup, cinnamon, and salt.
Slowly add veggie broth until desired consistency has formed. If yours is super thick you may need to add more.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Blend until creamy and smooth.
Pour into bowls (reheat if necessary) and top with coconut cream drizzle, crispy chickpeas and fresh cilantro.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Curried Butternut Squash Soup
Description: This is quite possibly the easiest and tastiest soup you will ever make... not exaggerating. And don't worry if you're lazy you can even buy pre-cubed butternut squash 😎 Just roast, then blend and you'll have a creamy, delicious soup in a matter of minutes! The slightly sweet butternut squash pairs perfectly with the curry spices, making for a perfectly warming fall/winter meal 😋 And don't skip out on the crispy chickpeas... trust me!

ingredients.Name: medium white or yellow onion, sliced

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 425 F.
Prepare maple marinade by mixing together olive oil, maple syrup, dijon mustard, and 1/2 tsp salt together in a small bowl.
Toss brussels, onions, and apples on a sheet pan and coat with maple marinade. Set aside.
Season chicken thighs with about 1 1/2 tsp salt and 1/2 tsp pepper.
Heat butter over medium-high heat in a large pan or cast iron skillet until melted.
Place chicken thighs flat side down and let sear for about 2 minutes without moving them, until a nice crispy golden brown crust forms.
Move brussels sprout mixture to the sides of the sheet pan making room in the center for the chicken thighs.
Remove chicken thighs from pan (without flipping) and place them on the sheet pan crispy side up.
Bake sheet pan in the oven for about 20 minutes, or until chicken thighs are 165 F in the center.
Remove from oven and season with additional salt + pepper (if necessary).
Garnish chicken with fresh rosemary and serve with mashed sweet potatoes and cranberry sauce. Enjoy!

***NOTE: You can also double the portions of the maple marinade and use it to coat the chicken thighs as well before baking them in the oven. I personally prefer the contrast of sweet and salty so I leave my chicken as is but this would be tasty too!

Creator: KITK
Name: Crispy Baked Chicken Thighs w/ Brussels Sprout Hash
Description: If you're in the mood for a simple fall chicken dinner thats packed with flavor and easy to make, this is the dinner for you! The slightly sweet maple roasted brussels sprout hash pairs perfectly with the crispy salty chicken thighs 😋 You're going to be making this one on repeat... trust me!

ingredients.Name: baby potatoes, halved if on the larger size
one head of broccoli, cut into florets

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400 F.
In a medium bowl toss potatoes with 1 tbs olive oil, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. Spread on a sheet pan and bake for 10 minutes.
In the same bowl toss broccoli with 1 tbs olive oil, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. Set aside.
Season chicken breasts on both sides with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Heat butter and 1 tbs olive oil in a pan over medium-high heat.
Once pan is hot, add chicken breasts and sear for about 2 minutes on each side. Remove from heat and set aside.
After 10 minutes, remove potatoes from the oven and add broccoli to the sheet pan. Stir to combine, then push potatoes and broccoli to the edges of the pan.
Add chicken breasts to the center of the sheet pan and bake for 20 minutes, or until chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165 F.
Meanwhile, prepare the dijon cream sauce.
Melt butter in a small saucepan over medium heat. Then add minced garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 1 minute.
Stir in chicken broth and dijon mustard. Then whisk in coconut cream, salt and pepper.
Serve everything together, topping chicken, veggies and potatoes with dijon cream sauce.
Top with fresh parsley. Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Dijon Cream Chicken & Veggies
Description: Creamy dijon cream sauce pairs perfectly with Italian-season chicken and tender potatoes and veggies! The best part? It all comes together on one sheet pan for an easy + healthy weeknight dinner!

ingredients.Name: boneless skinless chicken breast, cut into cubes
medium sweet potatoes, peeled and cubes
rice wine vinegar (or sub apple cider vinegar)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400 F. Line 1 XL sheet pan (or 2 regular-sized sheet pans) with parchment paper.
Prepare sauce by mixing ingredients together in the mixing bowl. Reserve 1/4 cup of the sauce in a small bowl for topping.
Add chicken pieces to the bowl and mix well so that all of the pieces are coated. Place bowl in the fridge to let chicken marinate while you prepare the veggies.
**Option to let the chicken marinate for up to 8 hours if you prep ahead of time, otherwise 15-20 minutes is fine.
Toss sweet potatoes on one side of sheet pan (or use one sheet pan) and season with oil, salt/pepper.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli to the same side of the sheet pan, season with additional oil, salt/pepper and toss to mix.
Add chicken pieces to the other side of the sheet pan (or to the second sheet pan if using) and season with salt/pepper.
Place sheet pan(s) back in the oven and bake for 20 minutes, or until chicken reaches internal temp of 165F.
Serve chicken over bed of broccoli and sweet potatoes and top with reserved peanut sauce.
Garnish with chopped peanuts, green onions and sesame seeds.
Enjoy!

Creator: KITK
Name: Thai Peanut Chicken and Veggies
Description: Tender chicken pieces coated in peanut sauce and roasted veggies makes for a flavorful, healthy dinner. And the best part? It comes together in just 30 minutes on one sheet pan! You're definitely going to want to save this one and give it a try :)

ingredients.Name: scallions, halved lengthwise and finely chopped (plus more for garnish)
minced ginger (I used frozen ginger cubes for a shortcut)

directions.Direction: Preheat oven to 400 F.
Bring a large pot of water to a boil, then add the baby potatoes and boil for about 20 - 25 minutes or until fork tender.
Drain and let potatoes cool for about 5 minutes. Then toss potatoes on a sheet pan and smash them flat using a piece of parchment paper and round-bottom glass to prevent sticking (see reel).
Once smashed, spray potatoes with oil and top each one with a sprinkle of salt + pepper.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until golden and crispy.
Meanwhile prepare the sauce by mixing sauce ingredients together in a small bowl. Make sure the bowl is big enough to dunk your chicken thighs in - my preferred method of coating :)
Reserve a few tablespoons of sauce in a separate bowl.
